<TITLE> Doctor accuses Kaiser Hamid of hitting him with pistol </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 30 (bdnews24.com)  Former national footballer Kaiser Hamid has been accused of hitting a doctor from Shishu Hospital on the head with a pistol Saturday night. Dr M Aminul Islam was admitted to Suhrawardi Hospital following the incident. "Last night I went to a petrol station near Asad Gate to fill up my car. When I parked the car in the queue another vehicle suddenly jumped in front of me," Aminul told bdnews24.com. "I protested the move with some others, but a passenger in the vehicle started arguing with me." "I identified the man as Kaiser Bhai and said 'we didn't expect this from you'." "Then he held up his pistol and said 'did you expect this'. He then hit me on the head with the pistol," said Aminul. Hamid denied the allegation to bdnews24.com, claiming the doctor was injured when he fell in a scuffle with his driver. The injured doctor said Mohammadpur Police Station refused to file a case without a doctor's certificate. Kaiser also denies possession of a pistol during the incident. bdnew
